// Rule of thumb
// async void: Only for top-level event handlers
// async Task: For all other methods
// async Task<T>: When you need to return a value`}]}]},bv={id:"csharp-linq",name:"LINQ (Language Integrated Query)",questions:[{id:"q1",question:"What is LINQ and why is it important in C#?",answer:"LINQ (Language Integrated Query) provides a uniform way to query different data sources using C# syntax. It works with objects (LINQ to Objects), databases (LINQ to SQL/Entity Framework), XML (LINQ to XML), and more. It's important because it provides type-safe, readable queries with compile-time checking and IntelliSense support.",codeSnippets:[{language:"csharp",code:`using System;
